## (3) "Synthetic Exclusion Lemma": REFUTED

The claimed proof-gap does not exist; both of its legs fail against the
shipped text:

- *"The spec never defines `materialized_size` formally"* — Book I §3.4
  defines it in its first paragraph: every materialized node counts 1, an
  unresolved hash leaf counts **exactly 1**, a materialized REF counts 2,
  `size(APPLY) = 1 + size(left) + size(right)`. The metric is over the
  current term, synthetic nodes included — no exclusion lemma is needed
  or implied.
- The R-S counterexample shape ("size +2 for 1 ATP") uses the **v0.4
  price**. v0.5 §3.4 prices `cost(R-S) = 1 + size(z)`. Recount under the
  defined metric: before = 3 APPLY + ⟨S⟩ + f + g + z; after = 3 APPLY +
  f + g + 2z; net growth = `size(z) − 1 < 1 + size(z) = cost`. The
  one-line theorem justification in §3.4 ("кожна дія коштує строго більше,
  ніж додає розміру") is exactly this per-rule lemma, proved in the
  Gemini gate review and re-derived by DeepSeek (both cited in §3.4 and
  warranted).
- The §3.4 budget-ordering worry is already settled law: "ATP budget
  check precedes firing; `spent` never exceeds `atp`; failed firings are
  not charged" (Codex follow-up, 2026-07, settled point in this README).

The reviewer audited "from the spec text alone" with Book I in the pack;
the definition was in the named section. Rejected.

## (4) Governance analytics: ACCEPTED (P3) — filed upstream

The four tunnel-rule failure modes and the DAG/key analyses are the first
serious institutional critique of the warrant layer and belong to the
warrant project, not this spec. Filed as issues on s0fractal/warrant:
evidence-foreclosure + interpretation lock-in (with the precedent
correction below), root-inclusion policy for multi-root stores +
missing-blob semantics, and single-key trust (rotation/threshold).

One precedent correction: the corpus already refutes the strictest
reading of interpretation lock-in. ADR-004 was opened over a settled
point using an existing artifact — the adjudication accepted "the shipped
artifact itself" as new evidence. The operative standard is *new
demonstrable consequence*, not *new bytes*. That reading should be
codified upstream, which is what the issue asks.

